      • addPhrase

        public AbstractPrintQuery addPhrase(String _key,
                           String _phraseStmt)
                             throws EFapsException
        Add a Phrase to this PrintQuery. A Phrase is something like: "$<attribute[LastName]> - $<attribute[FirstName]>" This would return " John - Doe". One Phrase can contain various selects as defined for addSelect(String...) and string to connect them.
        Parameters:
        _key - key the phrase can be accessed
        _phraseStmt - phrase to add
        Returns:
        this PrintQuery
        Throws:
        EFapsException - on error

      • addSelect

        public AbstractPrintQuery addSelect(SelectBuilder... _selectBldrs)
                             throws EFapsException
        Add an select to the PrintQuery. A select is something like: class[Emperador_Products_ClassFloorLaminate].linkto[SurfaceAttrId].attribute[Value]
        The use of the key words like "class" etc is mandatory. Contrary to addPhrase(String, String) the values will not be parsed! The values will not be editable.
        Parameters:
        _selectBldrs - selectBuilder to be added
        Returns:
        this PrintQuery
        Throws:
        EFapsException - on error

      • addSelect

        public AbstractPrintQuery addSelect(String... _selectStmts)
                             throws EFapsException
        Add an select to the PrintQuery. A select is something like: class[Emperador_Products_ClassFloorLaminate].linkto[SurfaceAttrId].attribute[Value]
        The use of the key words like "class" etc is mandatory. Contrary to addPhrase(String, String) the values will not be parsed! The values will not be editable.
        Parameters:
        _selectStmts - selectStatments to be added
        Returns:
        this PrintQuery
        Throws:
        EFapsException - on error
